# Day 3 - TCP/IP Model and Encapsulation

## Objective

Understand how data travels from one computer to another using the TCP/IP model and how encapsulation works.

---

# TCP/IP Model

| Layer | Responsibility |
|--------|----------------|
| Application | Provides services to user applications (HTTP, HTTPS, DNS, FTP, SMTP) |
| Transport | End-to-end communication using TCP or UDP |
| Network | Logical addressing and routing using IP |
| Data Link | Physical addressing using MAC addresses |
| Physical | Transmission of bits over the communication medium |

---

# Encapsulation

As data moves down the TCP/IP stack, each layer adds its own header.

Data

↓

Segment (TCP Header)

↓

Packet (IP Header)

↓

Frame (MAC Header)

↓

Bits

At the receiving end, headers are removed in reverse order (Decapsulation).

